(46, 4, 'Testing React Apps', 
 'The "Testing React Apps" module introduces you to techniques for ensuring your React components work as expected. It explains various testing tools and methodologies including Jest and React Testing Library. Detailed examples demonstrate how to write unit tests and integration tests for your components. The lesson includes exercises to test component behavior, state changes, and user interactions. The module emphasizes the importance of testing for maintaining code quality and reliability. It also discusses strategies for test organization and coverage. By the end, you will be equipped to write comprehensive tests for your React applications.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(47, 4, 'Deployment Strategies', 
 'In the "Deployment Strategies" module, you will learn how to prepare and deploy React applications to production. It explains different deployment options such as static hosting and cloud services. Detailed examples illustrate the process of building, optimizing, and deploying a React app. The lesson includes exercises that guide you through setting up a deployment pipeline. The module emphasizes best practices for ensuring security and performance in production. It also covers troubleshooting common deployment issues. By the end, you will be ready to deploy your React applications with confidence.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(48, 4, 'Bonus: Advanced Performance Optimization in React', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced Performance Optimization in React" focuses on techniques to further enhance the speed of your applications. It explains how to analyze and optimize component rendering and asset loading. Detailed examples show how to use memoization and code-splitting for improved performance. The lesson includes exercises to measure performance gains using browser tools. The module emphasizes the importance of optimizing both code and network resources. It also discusses best practices for maintaining high performance in complex applications. By the end, you will have advanced strategies to optimize your React app’s performance.',
 12, 1, 299, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 5: Data Science with Python (Modules 49-60)
(49, 5, 'Introduction to Data Science', 
 'In the "Introduction to Data Science" module, you will be introduced to the exciting world of data analysis. It explains the overall process of data collection, cleaning, and interpretation. Detailed examples illustrate the key concepts and tools used in data science. The lesson includes exercises to work with small datasets and visualize basic trends. The module emphasizes the interdisciplinary nature of data science and its real-world applications. It also discusses the importance of statistical reasoning and critical analysis. By the end, you will have a clear understanding of what data science entails and its potential impact.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(50, 5, 'Python for Data Science', 
 'The "Python for Data Science" module focuses on the essential libraries and tools used for data analysis. It explains how libraries such as NumPy and pandas simplify data manipulation. Detailed examples demonstrate the use of these libraries in practical scenarios. The lesson includes exercises to clean, transform, and analyze datasets. The module emphasizes the importance of writing efficient and readable code. It also discusses best practices for handling large volumes of data. By the end, you will be proficient in using Python as a tool for data science tasks.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(51, 5, 'Data Analysis with Pandas', 
 'In the "Data Analysis with Pandas" module, you will dive deep into one of Python’s most powerful libraries for data manipulation. It explains how to use DataFrames to organize and analyze data. Detailed examples illustrate methods for filtering, grouping, and aggregating data. The lesson includes exercises that challenge you to solve real-world data problems. The module emphasizes the flexibility and speed of pandas for data analysis. It also covers common data cleaning techniques to prepare your datasets. By the end, you will be confident in using pandas to derive insights from data.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(52, 5, 'Data Visualization with Matplotlib', 
 'The "Data Visualization with Matplotlib" module teaches you how to create informative charts and graphs. It explains the basic concepts of plotting data and customizing visualizations. Detailed examples demonstrate how to generate line plots, bar charts, and scatter plots. The lesson includes exercises to help you present data in a clear and engaging way. The module emphasizes the importance of visual storytelling in data science. It also discusses styling and formatting options to improve the presentation of your plots. By the end, you will be able to create compelling visualizations with Matplotlib.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(53, 5, 'Statistical Analysis', 
 'In the "Statistical Analysis" module, you will learn the fundamentals of statistics and how they apply to data science. It explains key concepts such as mean, median, variance, and standard deviation. Detailed examples illustrate how to perform statistical tests and interpret their results. The lesson includes exercises that challenge you to apply statistical methods to real data. The module emphasizes the importance of statistical reasoning in making informed decisions. It also covers hypothesis testing and confidence intervals. By the end, you will have the statistical tools needed to analyze data effectively.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(54, 5, 'Machine Learning Introduction', 
 'The "Machine Learning Introduction" module provides an overview of fundamental machine learning concepts. It explains various learning paradigms such as supervised and unsupervised learning. Detailed examples illustrate how algorithms learn from data to make predictions. The lesson includes exercises to demonstrate the basics of model training and evaluation. The module emphasizes the iterative nature of machine learning development. It also discusses challenges and considerations in building accurate models. By the end, you will be ready to explore more advanced machine learning topics.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(55, 5, 'Data Cleaning Techniques', 
 'In the "Data Cleaning Techniques" module, you will learn methods to prepare raw data for analysis. It explains how to handle missing values, outliers, and inconsistencies in datasets. Detailed examples demonstrate various techniques for cleaning and preprocessing data. The lesson includes exercises to practice transforming messy data into a usable format. The module emphasizes the importance of clean data for reliable analysis. It also covers automated tools and best practices for data cleaning. By the end, you will be equipped to ensure your datasets are accurate and consistent.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(56, 5, 'Feature Engineering', 
 'The "Feature Engineering" module focuses on transforming raw data into features that enhance model performance. It explains how to create new variables and select the most relevant ones. Detailed examples illustrate techniques such as scaling, encoding, and extraction. The lesson includes exercises that encourage creative thinking in feature design. The module emphasizes the role of domain knowledge in engineering useful features. It also discusses methods for evaluating feature importance. By the end, you will be capable of improving your models through effective feature engineering.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(57, 5, 'Model Evaluation', 
 'In the "Model Evaluation" module, you will learn how to assess the performance of your data science models. It explains various metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score. Detailed examples demonstrate how to use validation techniques like cross-validation. The lesson includes exercises to compare different models and choose the best one. The module emphasizes the importance of unbiased evaluation in machine learning. It also discusses common pitfalls and how to avoid overfitting. By the end, you will have the skills to critically evaluate your models.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(58, 5, 'Working with Big Data', 
 'The "Working with Big Data" module introduces you to tools and techniques for handling large datasets. It explains how to use frameworks and distributed computing solutions to manage big data. Detailed examples illustrate the challenges and solutions in processing data at scale. The lesson includes exercises that expose you to real-world big data scenarios. The module emphasizes performance optimization and efficient data storage. It also covers the integration of big data tools with Python. By the end, you will be prepared to tackle big data challenges in your projects.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(59, 5, 'Project: Data Analysis', 
 'In the "Project: Data Analysis" module, you will apply your data science skills to a comprehensive project. It guides you through the process of analyzing a real dataset from start to finish. Detailed examples illustrate how to collect, clean, visualize, and model the data. The lesson includes step-by-step exercises that simulate a professional data analysis workflow. The module emphasizes practical problem solving and effective communication of insights. It also covers best practices for documenting your work. By the end, you will have completed a project that demonstrates your proficiency in data analysis.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(60, 5, 'Bonus: Advanced Data Wrangling Techniques', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced Data Wrangling Techniques" delves into complex data transformation methods. It explains advanced methods for merging, reshaping, and cleaning datasets. Detailed examples demonstrate techniques that handle intricate data issues. The lesson includes exercises to practice advanced wrangling on challenging datasets. The module emphasizes the importance of robust data preparation in achieving accurate analyses. It also discusses automation tools for streamlining data wrangling tasks. By the end, you will be equipped with sophisticated techniques to master complex data transformations.',
 12, 1, 350, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 6: Machine Learning Basics (Modules 61-72)
(61, 6, 'Introduction to Machine Learning', 
 'In the "Introduction to Machine Learning" module, you will be introduced to the core concepts of machine learning. It explains the difference between traditional programming and learning-based models. Detailed examples illustrate various machine learning paradigms. The lesson includes exercises to help you understand the basic workflow of model building. The module emphasizes the impact of machine learning on real-world applications. It also covers key terminology and foundational algorithms. By the end, you will have a clear overview of the machine learning landscape.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(62, 6, 'Supervised Learning', 
 'The "Supervised Learning" module focuses on techniques where the model is trained using labeled data. It explains the concepts of regression and classification through detailed examples. The lesson includes practical exercises that demonstrate how to build and evaluate supervised models. The module emphasizes the importance of training data quality and proper evaluation metrics. It also discusses challenges such as overfitting and underfitting. Best practices for model tuning are presented throughout the module. By the end, you will be proficient in building supervised learning models.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(63, 6, 'Unsupervised Learning', 
 'In the "Unsupervised Learning" module, you will learn techniques to discover hidden patterns in unlabeled data. It explains clustering and dimensionality reduction with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that demonstrate how to segment data and identify inherent structures. The module emphasizes exploratory data analysis and data visualization. It also discusses the challenges of evaluating unsupervised models. Best practices for selecting algorithms based on data characteristics are highlighted. By the end, you will understand how to apply unsupervised learning methods effectively.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(64, 6, 'Regression Analysis', 
 'The "Regression Analysis" module provides an in-depth look at regression models for predicting continuous outcomes. It explains the mathematical foundations behind linear and non-linear regression. Detailed examples illustrate how to fit models to data and interpret coefficients. The lesson includes exercises to practice model evaluation and diagnostics. The module emphasizes the importance of assumptions and model validation. It also discusses techniques to handle multicollinearity and heteroscedasticity. By the end, you will be able to build and assess regression models confidently.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(65, 6, 'Classification Techniques', 
 'In the "Classification Techniques" module, you will learn how to assign labels to data points using various algorithms. It explains methods such as logistic regression, decision trees, and support vector machines. Detailed examples demonstrate how to build classification models and evaluate their performance. The lesson includes exercises to handle imbalanced datasets and optimize model parameters. The module emphasizes the importance of accuracy, precision, and recall in classification tasks. It also covers the use of confusion matrices for performance analysis. By the end, you will have the skills to implement effective classification solutions.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(66, 6, 'Model Evaluation', 
 'The "Model Evaluation" module in Machine Learning covers techniques for assessing model performance. It explains various metrics including accuracy, ROC-AUC, and mean squared error. Detailed examples illustrate how to use cross-validation and holdout sets effectively. The lesson includes exercises that focus on comparing models to choose the best one. The module emphasizes the importance of unbiased evaluation in building reliable models. It also discusses challenges such as data leakage and overfitting. By the end, you will be able to evaluate your machine learning models with confidence.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(67, 6, 'Overfitting and Underfitting', 
 'In the "Overfitting and Underfitting" module, you will learn to recognize and correct common pitfalls in machine learning. It explains how models can perform poorly when too complex or too simple relative to the data. Detailed examples illustrate diagnostic techniques and remedies such as regularization. The lesson includes exercises to balance model complexity and generalization. The module emphasizes the importance of validation techniques in preventing overfitting. It also covers strategies such as cross-validation and parameter tuning. By the end, you will be able to design models that generalize well to new data.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(68, 6, 'Feature Scaling', 
 'The "Feature Scaling" module focuses on techniques for normalizing data to improve model performance. It explains the importance of scaling features to ensure fair comparisons during training. Detailed examples demonstrate methods such as normalization and standardization. The lesson includes exercises to apply scaling techniques on sample datasets. The module emphasizes how scaling can accelerate convergence in many algorithms. It also discusses potential issues when features are not properly scaled. By the end, you will be proficient in preparing your data for optimal machine learning performance.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(69, 6, 'Ensemble Methods', 
 'In the "Ensemble Methods" module, you will learn how to combine multiple models to achieve better predictions. It explains techniques such as bagging, boosting, and stacking. Detailed examples illustrate how ensemble approaches can reduce variance and improve accuracy. The lesson includes exercises to implement ensemble models on benchmark datasets. The module emphasizes the benefits of leveraging multiple algorithms together. It also covers common pitfalls and how to interpret ensemble results. By the end, you will have a strong grasp of ensemble strategies in machine learning.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(70, 6, 'Neural Networks Introduction', 
 'The "Neural Networks Introduction" module provides a basic overview of artificial neural networks and their architecture. It explains the structure of neurons, layers, and activation functions with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to build simple neural network models using Python libraries. The module emphasizes the power of neural networks for handling complex patterns in data. It also discusses the historical development and applications of neural networks. Best practices for training and evaluating networks are presented. By the end, you will have an introductory understanding of neural network design.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(71, 6, 'Practical ML Project', 
 'In the "Practical ML Project" module, you will apply machine learning concepts to a real-world project. It guides you through the complete pipeline from data preprocessing to model deployment. Detailed examples illustrate problem formulation, model selection, and evaluation. The lesson includes hands-on exercises that simulate a production environment. The module emphasizes collaboration, documentation, and iterative improvement. It also covers troubleshooting common issues encountered during projects. By the end, you will have completed a machine learning project that showcases your practical skills.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(72, 6, 'Bonus: Advanced Hyperparameter Tuning', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced Hyperparameter Tuning" focuses on optimizing model performance through careful parameter adjustment. It explains techniques such as grid search and randomized search with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that demonstrate how to improve model performance using tuning strategies. The module emphasizes the importance of balancing bias and variance. It also discusses advanced topics like Bayesian optimization. By the end, you will be equipped with sophisticated methods to fine-tune your machine learning models.',
 12, 1, 450, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 7: Cybersecurity Fundamentals (Modules 73-84)
(73, 7, 'Introduction to Cybersecurity', 
 'In the "Introduction to Cybersecurity" module, you will learn the basic principles of protecting information and systems. It explains common threats and the need for a secure digital environment. Detailed examples illustrate how cybersecurity practices safeguard data. The lesson includes exercises that simulate risk assessment scenarios. The module emphasizes the importance of awareness and proactive security measures. It also covers the impact of cybersecurity on individuals and organizations. By the end, you will have a solid understanding of the cybersecurity landscape.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(74, 7, 'Types of Cyber Threats', 
 'The "Types of Cyber Threats" module provides an overview of various digital attacks such as malware, phishing, and ransomware. It explains how each threat operates and the damage it can cause. Detailed examples illustrate real-world incidents and their consequences. The lesson includes exercises to identify and classify different threats. The module emphasizes the evolving nature of cyber threats and the need for continuous learning. It also discusses preventive measures and best practices. By the end, you will be able to recognize and respond to various cybersecurity threats.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(75, 7, 'Network Security Basics', 
 'In the "Network Security Basics" module, you will learn how to protect network infrastructure from unauthorized access. It explains key concepts such as firewalls, VPNs, and secure protocols. Detailed examples demonstrate how network security is implemented in real-world systems. The lesson includes exercises that involve configuring basic security settings. The module emphasizes the importance of monitoring and maintaining network security. It also covers common vulnerabilities and how to mitigate them. By the end, you will have a foundational understanding of network security measures.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(76, 7, 'Encryption and Cryptography', 
 'The "Encryption and Cryptography" module focuses on techniques used to secure data through encryption. It explains how cryptographic algorithms protect information from unauthorized access. Detailed examples illustrate how encryption is applied in everyday technology. The lesson includes exercises to understand key management and decryption processes. The module emphasizes the importance of strong encryption in maintaining data privacy. It also discusses real-world applications and challenges of cryptography. By the end, you will be able to explain how encryption supports cybersecurity.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(77, 7, 'Secure Coding Practices', 
 'In the "Secure Coding Practices" module, you will learn how to write code that minimizes vulnerabilities. It explains best practices for developing secure software and avoiding common pitfalls. Detailed examples demonstrate how to prevent security issues such as SQL injection and cross-site scripting. The lesson includes exercises that reinforce secure programming techniques. The module emphasizes the role of secure coding in the overall cybersecurity strategy. It also covers tools and methods for testing code security. By the end, you will be able to write robust code that resists cyber attacks.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(78, 7, 'Firewalls and VPNs', 
 'The "Firewalls and VPNs" module teaches you about the technologies that protect network traffic and secure remote access. It explains how firewalls filter network traffic and how VPNs encrypt data transmissions. Detailed examples illustrate how these tools are configured and maintained. The lesson includes exercises to set up basic firewall rules and VPN connections. The module emphasizes the importance of layered security in protecting networks. It also discusses the challenges of managing network access in diverse environments. By the end, you will understand how to implement firewalls and VPNs effectively.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(79, 7, 'Vulnerability Assessment', 
 'In the "Vulnerability Assessment" module, you will learn techniques to identify and mitigate security weaknesses. It explains the process of scanning systems for vulnerabilities and assessing potential risks. Detailed examples illustrate common vulnerabilities and how they can be exploited. The lesson includes exercises to practice using vulnerability assessment tools. The module emphasizes proactive security measures and continuous monitoring. It also covers reporting and remediation strategies. By the end, you will be prepared to conduct effective vulnerability assessments.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(80, 7, 'Incident Response', 
 'The "Incident Response" module focuses on the steps to take when a security breach occurs. It explains the importance of having an incident response plan and the roles of different team members. Detailed examples illustrate real-world incident response scenarios. The lesson includes exercises to develop and test response strategies. The module emphasizes the need for quick and effective action to mitigate damage. It also discusses communication and recovery processes after an incident. By the end, you will be able to formulate a solid incident response strategy.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(81, 7, 'Security Policies', 
 'In the "Security Policies" module, you will learn how to develop and implement policies that enforce cybersecurity best practices. It explains the role of policies in guiding user behavior and protecting data. Detailed examples illustrate how effective policies are structured and communicated. The lesson includes exercises to draft sample security policies for an organization. The module emphasizes the importance of regular policy reviews and updates. It also covers the impact of policies on compliance and risk management. By the end, you will have the knowledge to develop robust security policies.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(82, 7, 'Ethical Hacking Overview', 
 'The "Ethical Hacking Overview" module introduces you to the principles of penetration testing and ethical hacking. It explains how security professionals use hacking techniques to find vulnerabilities before malicious hackers do. Detailed examples illustrate common tools and methodologies used in ethical hacking. The lesson includes exercises that simulate ethical hacking scenarios. The module emphasizes the legal and ethical considerations of penetration testing. It also discusses certifications and career paths in ethical hacking. By the end, you will understand the importance of ethical hacking in cybersecurity.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(83, 7, 'Real-world Cybersecurity Cases', 
 'In the "Real-world Cybersecurity Cases" module, you will analyze notable security breaches and how they were addressed. It explains the circumstances behind several high-profile cyber attacks. Detailed examples provide insights into the lessons learned from each case. The lesson includes discussions and exercises to evaluate the effectiveness of different responses. The module emphasizes the importance of learning from past incidents. It also covers trends and emerging threats highlighted by these cases. By the end, you will be able to apply real-world insights to improve security practices.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(84, 7, 'Bonus: Advanced Penetration Testing Techniques', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced Penetration Testing Techniques" dives deep into sophisticated methods for assessing system vulnerabilities. It explains advanced tools and techniques that ethical hackers use to simulate real attacks. Detailed examples illustrate the step-by-step process of conducting a comprehensive penetration test. The lesson includes exercises that challenge you to think like an attacker and then defend against those tactics. The module emphasizes continuous learning and adapting to new threats. It also discusses the importance of documentation and reporting. By the end, you will have advanced strategies to enhance your penetration testing skills.',
 12, 1, 300, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 8: HTML & CSS for Beginners (Modules 85-96)
(85, 8, 'Introduction to HTML', 
 'In the "Introduction to HTML" module, you will learn the basic structure of web pages using HTML. It explains how HTML tags create the skeleton of a website. Detailed examples illustrate how to build a simple page using headings, paragraphs, and links. The lesson includes exercises to write your own HTML code from scratch. The module emphasizes the importance of semantic markup for accessibility. It also covers best practices for organizing HTML content. By the end, you will have a solid understanding of HTML fundamentals.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(86, 8, 'HTML Elements and Attributes', 
 'The "HTML Elements and Attributes" module focuses on the various components that make up an HTML document. It explains how elements work together and how attributes modify their behavior. Detailed examples demonstrate the usage of common attributes such as class, id, and style. The lesson includes exercises to practice applying attributes to HTML elements. The module emphasizes the importance of proper attribute usage for styling and scripting. It also discusses accessibility considerations in element design. By the end, you will be proficient in using HTML elements and attributes to create structured web pages.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(87, 8, 'CSS Basics', 
 'In the "CSS Basics" module, you will be introduced to Cascading Style Sheets and how they control the look of web pages. It explains the syntax of CSS and how to apply styles to HTML elements. Detailed examples illustrate how to change colors, fonts, and layouts using CSS. The lesson includes exercises to style a basic HTML page. The module emphasizes the separation of content and presentation for better maintainability. It also covers inline, internal, and external styling methods. By the end, you will have a foundational understanding of CSS.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(88, 8, 'Styling with CSS', 
 'The "Styling with CSS" module goes deeper into advanced selectors and layout techniques. It explains how to use classes, ids, and pseudo-selectors to target specific elements. Detailed examples demonstrate responsive design principles and modern layout approaches. The lesson includes exercises to create stylish and dynamic web pages. The module emphasizes best practices for organizing CSS code and avoiding conflicts. It also discusses browser compatibility issues and debugging techniques. By the end, you will be able to apply advanced styling to enhance the visual appeal of your websites.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(89, 8, 'Responsive Design', 
 'In the "Responsive Design" module, you will learn how to build web pages that look great on any device. It explains the principles of fluid grids, flexible images, and media queries. Detailed examples illustrate how to adapt layouts for mobile, tablet, and desktop screens. The lesson includes exercises to practice creating responsive designs. The module emphasizes the importance of user experience and accessibility. It also covers best practices for testing responsiveness across different devices. By the end, you will be proficient in designing responsive web pages.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(90, 8, 'Flexbox Layout', 
 'The "Flexbox Layout" module introduces you to CSS Flexbox for building flexible and efficient layouts. It explains the properties and values that control flex container behavior. Detailed examples illustrate how to align and distribute space among items. The lesson includes exercises that challenge you to recreate common layout patterns using Flexbox. The module emphasizes simplicity and adaptability in layout design. It also covers best practices for cross-browser compatibility. By the end, you will be adept at using Flexbox to build modern web layouts.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(91, 8, 'Grid Layout', 
 'In the "Grid Layout" module, you will learn about the CSS Grid system for two-dimensional layouts. It explains how to define rows, columns, and grid areas to structure your page. Detailed examples demonstrate how to create complex layouts that are both flexible and responsive. The lesson includes exercises to design grid-based layouts for various scenarios. The module emphasizes the power of CSS Grid in modern web design. It also discusses best practices for combining grid and Flexbox. By the end, you will be able to build intricate layouts using CSS Grid.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(92, 8, 'Working with Images and Media', 
 'The "Working with Images and Media" module focuses on incorporating multimedia into your web pages. It explains how to embed images, videos, and audio with proper HTML and CSS techniques. Detailed examples illustrate how to optimize media for web performance and responsiveness. The lesson includes exercises to practice integrating different types of media. The module emphasizes accessibility and proper formatting for various devices. It also covers best practices for image optimization and responsive media. By the end, you will be skilled at handling images and media in web design.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(93, 8, 'Web Accessibility Basics', 
 'In the "Web Accessibility Basics" module, you will learn how to make websites usable by everyone. It explains the importance of accessible design for users with disabilities. Detailed examples illustrate techniques such as semantic HTML, ARIA roles, and keyboard navigation. The lesson includes exercises to evaluate and improve the accessibility of web pages. The module emphasizes legal and ethical considerations in web development. It also covers common accessibility testing tools and guidelines. By the end, you will be equipped to create inclusive web experiences.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(94, 8, 'Building a Simple Web Page', 
 'The "Building a Simple Web Page" module guides you through the process of creating a complete website from scratch. It explains how to structure content, style elements, and add interactivity. Detailed examples illustrate the entire workflow from planning to execution. The lesson includes hands-on exercises that help you build your own web page. The module emphasizes the integration of HTML, CSS, and basic JavaScript. It also covers troubleshooting common issues during development. By the end, you will have built a fully functional and visually appealing web page.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(95, 8, 'Project: Personal Portfolio', 
 'In the "Project: Personal Portfolio" module, you will apply your HTML and CSS skills to create a personal portfolio website. It explains how to showcase your work, skills, and achievements effectively. Detailed examples illustrate the layout and design elements that make a portfolio stand out. The lesson includes exercises that simulate real-world project development. The module emphasizes the importance of personal branding and responsive design. It also discusses best practices for content organization and visual appeal. By the end, you will have a portfolio site that reflects your creativity and technical abilities.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(96, 8, 'Bonus: Advanced CSS Animations', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced CSS Animations" explores techniques to bring your web pages to life. It explains how to create smooth and engaging animations using CSS transitions and keyframes. Detailed examples demonstrate how to animate elements for dynamic effects. The lesson includes exercises to experiment with different animation techniques. The module emphasizes performance optimization and compatibility across browsers. It also covers creative uses of animations in user interfaces. By the end, you will be able to enhance your web pages with sophisticated CSS animations.',
 12, 1, 150, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 9: DevOps and CI/CD (Modules 97-108)
(97, 9, 'Introduction to DevOps', 
 'In the "Introduction to DevOps" module, you will learn the core principles of the DevOps culture and methodology. It explains how development and operations collaborate to improve efficiency. Detailed examples illustrate how automation and continuous integration streamline workflows. The lesson includes exercises that simulate a DevOps environment. The module emphasizes the importance of communication and collaboration in achieving rapid delivery. It also covers the impact of DevOps on organizational performance. By the end, you will understand the foundations of DevOps and its benefits.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(98, 9, 'Understanding CI/CD', 
 'The "Understanding CI/CD" module focuses on continuous integration and continuous deployment practices. It explains how automated pipelines improve code quality and reduce deployment time. Detailed examples illustrate the steps involved in setting up CI/CD pipelines. The lesson includes exercises to simulate integration and deployment processes. The module emphasizes the benefits of early error detection and rapid feedback loops. It also covers common tools used in CI/CD workflows. By the end, you will be proficient in implementing CI/CD practices in your projects.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(99, 9, 'Version Control with Git', 
 'In the "Version Control with Git" module, you will learn the basics of using Git for source control. It explains how Git helps track changes, manage branches, and collaborate with others. Detailed examples illustrate common Git commands and workflows. The lesson includes exercises that reinforce version control concepts. The module emphasizes the importance of commit history and branching strategies. It also covers best practices for collaborative development using Git. By the end, you will have a strong understanding of version control with Git.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(100, 9, 'Continuous Integration Tools', 
 'The "Continuous Integration Tools" module introduces you to various software tools that facilitate CI processes. It explains the features and benefits of popular CI tools like Jenkins, Travis CI, and CircleCI. Detailed examples illustrate how to set up and configure these tools. The lesson includes exercises that simulate integrating code changes automatically. The module emphasizes the importance of automation in improving code quality. It also discusses integration with version control systems and testing frameworks. By the end, you will be able to select and configure a CI tool that meets your needs.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(101, 9, 'Continuous Deployment Strategies', 
 'In the "Continuous Deployment Strategies" module, you will learn how to automate the release process for your applications. It explains the steps involved in deploying code changes to production environments. Detailed examples demonstrate how to handle rollbacks and zero-downtime deployments. The lesson includes exercises to design and implement deployment strategies. The module emphasizes the importance of monitoring and testing in deployment processes. It also covers best practices for secure and efficient deployments. By the end, you will be equipped to deploy applications continuously and reliably.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(102, 9, 'Containerization with Docker', 
 'The "Containerization with Docker" module teaches you how to package applications into containers for consistent deployment. It explains the benefits of containerization, including isolation and portability. Detailed examples illustrate how to create Docker images and run containers. The lesson includes exercises that involve building and managing containers. The module emphasizes how containers simplify deployment across different environments. It also covers best practices for optimizing container performance. By the end, you will have practical experience using Docker for containerization.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(103, 9, 'Orchestration with Kubernetes', 
 'In the "Orchestration with Kubernetes" module, you will learn how to manage containerized applications at scale. It explains the architecture of Kubernetes and how it automates deployment, scaling, and management. Detailed examples illustrate the creation of pods, services, and deployments. The lesson includes exercises that simulate managing a cluster of containers. The module emphasizes the importance of orchestration in modern DevOps practices. It also discusses best practices for maintaining a Kubernetes cluster. By the end, you will be proficient in using Kubernetes to orchestrate containerized applications.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(104, 9, 'Infrastructure as Code', 
 'The "Infrastructure as Code" module focuses on automating infrastructure provisioning using code. It explains how tools like Terraform and CloudFormation can manage environments efficiently. Detailed examples illustrate how to write infrastructure code that is both reproducible and versioned. The lesson includes exercises to create and deploy infrastructure using code. The module emphasizes the benefits of treating infrastructure as part of the development process. It also covers best practices for managing and securing infrastructure code. By the end, you will be ready to implement infrastructure as code in your DevOps workflow.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(105, 9, 'Monitoring and Logging', 
 'In the "Monitoring and Logging" module, you will learn the importance of tracking application performance and behavior. It explains how monitoring tools and log management solutions help in proactive issue detection. Detailed examples illustrate the setup and use of popular monitoring systems. The lesson includes exercises to configure logging and analyze system metrics. The module emphasizes the role of monitoring in maintaining system reliability and performance. It also covers best practices for log retention and alerting. By the end, you will have the skills to monitor and troubleshoot your applications effectively.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(106, 9, 'Security in DevOps', 
 'The "Security in DevOps" module integrates security practices into the DevOps pipeline. It explains how to incorporate security checks throughout the development and deployment process. Detailed examples illustrate techniques such as automated security testing and vulnerability scanning. The lesson includes exercises to integrate security tools into CI/CD workflows. The module emphasizes the importance of a proactive security approach in DevOps. It also discusses compliance and regulatory considerations. By the end, you will be able to implement security measures seamlessly into your DevOps practices.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(107, 9, 'Case Study: DevOps in Action', 
 'In the "Case Study: DevOps in Action" module, you will analyze real-world examples of DevOps implementation. It explains how organizations have successfully integrated development and operations for better outcomes. Detailed examples provide insights into the challenges and successes experienced. The lesson includes discussions and exercises that evaluate different DevOps strategies. The module emphasizes lessons learned from real-world deployments. It also covers how to adapt these strategies to your own projects. By the end, you will have practical insights into the effective application of DevOps principles.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(108, 9, 'Bonus: Advanced Pipeline Optimization', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced Pipeline Optimization" focuses on refining CI/CD pipelines for maximum efficiency. It explains advanced techniques to reduce build times and improve reliability. Detailed examples illustrate how to optimize various stages of the pipeline. The lesson includes exercises to identify and eliminate bottlenecks. The module emphasizes continuous improvement and performance monitoring. It also covers strategies for integrating parallel processes and caching. By the end, you will have advanced methods to optimize your deployment pipelines.',
 12, 1, 350, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 10: Mobile App Development with Flutter (Modules 109-120)
(109, 10, 'Introduction to Flutter', 
 'In the "Introduction to Flutter" module, you will learn about the Flutter framework and its capabilities for mobile app development. It explains the benefits of using Flutter for creating cross-platform apps. Detailed examples illustrate how Flutter widgets form the building blocks of an application. The lesson includes exercises to set up your development environment and build simple interfaces. The module emphasizes the speed and flexibility of Flutter’s development cycle. It also covers key differences between Flutter and other mobile frameworks. By the end, you will be familiar with the basics of Flutter app development.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(110, 10, 'Dart Basics', 
 'The "Dart Basics" module introduces you to Dart, the programming language used with Flutter. It explains Dart’s syntax, data types, and control structures through detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to practice coding in Dart. The module emphasizes the importance of Dart in building efficient and responsive apps. It also discusses features that make Dart easy to learn for developers. Best practices for writing clean Dart code are covered throughout. By the end, you will have a strong foundation in Dart programming.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(111, 10, 'Flutter Widgets', 
 'In the "Flutter Widgets" module, you will explore the core widgets that make up Flutter applications. It explains how to use layout, text, and image widgets with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to create custom widgets and understand their properties. The module emphasizes the reusable nature of widgets for efficient UI development. It also covers stateful and stateless widget differences. Best practices for designing intuitive user interfaces are discussed. By the end, you will be able to build complex UIs using Flutter widgets.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(112, 10, 'Building Layouts', 
 'The "Building Layouts" module focuses on arranging Flutter widgets to create appealing user interfaces. It explains various layout widgets like Row, Column, and Stack with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to design responsive and adaptive layouts. The module emphasizes the importance of consistency and alignment in app design. It also covers techniques for managing spacing and positioning elements. Best practices for building flexible layouts are highlighted throughout. By the end, you will be proficient in constructing well-organized Flutter layouts.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(113, 10, 'State Management', 
 'In the "State Management" module, you will learn techniques for managing state in Flutter applications. It explains the differences between local and global state management with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to implement simple state management solutions. The module emphasizes the importance of maintaining a reactive user interface. It also discusses various approaches such as Provider and Bloc. Best practices for state management and data flow are covered extensively. By the end, you will be able to manage state effectively in your Flutter apps.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(114, 10, 'Navigation and Routing', 
 'The "Navigation and Routing" module teaches you how to move between screens in Flutter apps. It explains how to set up routes and pass data between pages with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that involve creating a multi-screen app. The module emphasizes the importance of a smooth user experience in navigation. It also covers techniques for managing the navigation stack and deep linking. Best practices for structuring app routes are discussed. By the end, you will be able to implement effective navigation in your Flutter applications.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(115, 10, 'API Integration', 
 'In the "API Integration" module, you will learn how to connect your Flutter app to external data sources. It explains how to use HTTP requests and parse JSON responses with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to integrate real-time data into your app. The module emphasizes the importance of handling asynchronous data and error management. It also covers best practices for secure and efficient API communication. Techniques for caching and updating data dynamically are discussed. By the end, you will be proficient in integrating APIs into your Flutter apps.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(116, 10, 'Animations in Flutter', 
 'The "Animations in Flutter" module explores how to add motion and interactivity to your app interfaces. It explains various animation techniques using Flutter’s built-in animation library. Detailed examples demonstrate how to create smooth transitions and interactive effects. The lesson includes exercises to experiment with different animation parameters. The module emphasizes the importance of animations in enhancing user engagement. It also covers performance considerations when implementing animations. By the end, you will have the skills to create compelling animations in your Flutter apps.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(117, 10, 'Testing Flutter Apps', 
 'In the "Testing Flutter Apps" module, you will learn about methods and tools for ensuring your app works as expected. It explains how to write unit tests and widget tests with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to practice testing different parts of a Flutter app. The module emphasizes the importance of maintaining code quality through continuous testing. It also covers best practices for automated testing in mobile development. Strategies for debugging and test-driven development are discussed. By the end, you will be prepared to implement comprehensive tests for your Flutter applications.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(118, 10, 'Deploying Flutter Apps', 
 'The "Deploying Flutter Apps" module guides you through the process of releasing your app to app stores. It explains how to prepare your app for production with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that cover app signing, build optimization, and store submission. The module emphasizes the importance of thorough testing before deployment. It also discusses strategies for handling updates and user feedback post-deployment. Best practices for deployment security and performance are highlighted. By the end, you will be ready to deploy your Flutter app confidently.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(119, 10, 'Project: Build a Mobile App', 
 'In the "Project: Build a Mobile App" module, you will apply your Flutter skills to develop a complete mobile application. It guides you through planning, coding, testing, and refining your app with detailed examples. The lesson includes hands-on exercises that simulate a real-world app development project. The module emphasizes creative problem solving and iterative design. It also covers collaboration, code reviews, and project documentation. By the end, you will have built a functional mobile app that demonstrates your proficiency in Flutter development.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(120, 10, 'Bonus: Advanced Flutter Performance Tips', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced Flutter Performance Tips" focuses on optimizing your mobile apps for speed and responsiveness. It explains advanced strategies such as widget recycling, lazy loading, and code splitting with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to measure and enhance app performance. The module emphasizes the importance of efficient resource management and minimizing render times. It also covers best practices for profiling and debugging performance issues. By the end, you will be equipped with advanced techniques to optimize your Flutter applications.',
 12, 1, 250, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 11: C++ for Beginners (Modules 121-132)
(121, 11, 'Introduction to C++', 
 'In the "Introduction to C++" module, you will learn the basics of the C++ programming language. It explains the history, syntax, and structure of C++ with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to write simple programs and understand compiler outputs. The module emphasizes the power and efficiency of C++ in system programming. It also covers differences between C++ and other programming languages. Best practices for writing readable and efficient C++ code are discussed. By the end, you will have a solid introduction to C++ and its core features.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(122, 11, 'Basic Syntax', 
 'The "Basic Syntax" module focuses on the fundamental syntax rules of C++. It explains data types, variables, and operators with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that help you practice writing syntactically correct code. The module emphasizes the importance of understanding syntax to avoid compilation errors. It also discusses common mistakes and how to fix them. Best practices for writing clean C++ code are covered throughout the module. By the end, you will be confident in using C++ syntax to build programs.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(123, 11, 'Data Types in C++', 
 'In the "Data Types in C++" module, you will explore the various data types available in C++. It explains the differences between primitive and complex data types with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to practice variable declaration and type conversion. The module emphasizes the importance of selecting appropriate data types for efficiency. It also covers concepts such as type casting and memory allocation. Best practices for managing data in C++ are discussed. By the end, you will be proficient in working with C++ data types.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(124, 11, 'Control Structures', 
 'The "Control Structures" module teaches you how to control the flow of execution in C++ programs. It explains conditional statements, loops, and branching with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that involve writing code with if-else statements and loops. The module emphasizes the importance of logical thinking and structured programming. It also covers nested control structures and error handling. Best practices for writing efficient control flow are discussed. By the end, you will be able to design C++ programs with complex logic effectively.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(125, 11, 'Functions in C++', 
 'In the "Functions in C++" module, you will learn how to create and use functions to organize your code. It explains the syntax of function declarations, definitions, and calls with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to build modular programs using functions. The module emphasizes the benefits of code reusability and clarity. It also covers parameter passing, return types, and recursion. Best practices for designing and organizing functions are discussed. By the end, you will have a solid grasp of function usage in C++.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(126, 11, 'Arrays and Strings', 
 'The "Arrays and Strings" module focuses on handling collections of data in C++. It explains how to declare, initialize, and manipulate arrays and strings with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that involve iterating through arrays and processing text data. The module emphasizes the importance of understanding memory management for arrays. It also covers common operations such as sorting and searching. Best practices for using arrays and strings effectively are discussed. By the end, you will be proficient in working with these fundamental data structures.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(127, 11, 'Pointers and Memory Management', 
 'In the "Pointers and Memory Management" module, you will learn about the concepts of pointers and dynamic memory allocation in C++. It explains how pointers work and how they are used to manipulate data directly. Detailed examples illustrate pointer arithmetic and memory allocation functions. The lesson includes exercises to practice using pointers safely and effectively. The module emphasizes the importance of proper memory management to avoid leaks and errors. It also discusses advanced topics such as pointer arithmetic and smart pointers. By the end, you will be comfortable working with pointers in C++.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(128, 11, 'Object-Oriented Concepts', 
 'The "Object-Oriented Concepts" module introduces you to the principles of object-oriented programming in C++. It explains concepts such as classes, objects, inheritance, and polymorphism with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to design and implement simple classes. The module emphasizes the benefits of encapsulation and code reusability. It also covers constructors, destructors, and access specifiers. Best practices for object-oriented design in C++ are discussed. By the end, you will be prepared to apply OOP techniques in your C++ programs.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(129, 11, 'Standard Template Library', 
 'In the "Standard Template Library" module, you will learn how to use the STL to simplify common programming tasks in C++. It explains how to use containers, iterators, and algorithms with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to work with vectors, lists, and maps. The module emphasizes the efficiency and flexibility provided by the STL. It also covers best practices for using templates and generic programming. By the end, you will be able to leverage the STL to write concise and efficient code.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(130, 11, 'Error Handling', 
 'The "Error Handling" module in C++ teaches you techniques for managing exceptions and errors gracefully. It explains the try-catch mechanism and how to throw exceptions with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that simulate error conditions and how to respond to them. The module emphasizes the importance of robust error handling in critical systems. It also covers best practices for designing error messages and logging. By the end, you will be able to implement comprehensive error handling in your C++ applications.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(131, 11, 'Project: Simple C++ App', 
 'In the "Project: Simple C++ App" module, you will apply your knowledge of C++ to build a complete, small-scale application. It guides you through the entire development process from planning to debugging with detailed examples. The lesson includes hands-on exercises that simulate real-world application development. The module emphasizes the importance of integrating multiple programming concepts effectively. It also discusses testing and iterative improvement during development. By the end, you will have created a working C++ application that demonstrates your skills.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(132, 11, 'Bonus: Advanced C++ Optimization', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced C++ Optimization" focuses on techniques to improve the performance of your C++ code. It explains optimization strategies such as loop unrolling, inline functions, and memory management best practices with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to benchmark and optimize sample applications. The module emphasizes the importance of writing efficient, high-performance code. It also covers profiling tools and techniques for identifying bottlenecks. By the end, you will have advanced strategies to optimize your C++ programs effectively.',
 12, 1, 200, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 12: Game Development with Unity (Modules 133-144)
(133, 12, 'Introduction to Unity', 
 'In the "Introduction to Unity" module, you will be introduced to the Unity game engine and its capabilities. It explains the Unity interface, asset management, and basic project setup with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to create a simple scene and navigate the editor. The module emphasizes the importance of understanding Unity’s workflow for game development. It also covers basic scripting concepts within Unity. Best practices for project organization are discussed. By the end, you will have a strong foundation to start developing games with Unity.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(134, 12, 'Unity Interface Basics', 
 'The "Unity Interface Basics" module focuses on familiarizing you with the Unity editor and its essential components. It explains how to use the Scene, Game, and Inspector windows effectively with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to customize the workspace and navigate the interface. The module emphasizes the importance of a well-organized development environment. It also covers tools for asset import and scene management. By the end, you will be comfortable with the Unity interface and ready to build complex scenes.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(135, 12, '2D Game Development', 
 'In the "2D Game Development" module, you will learn the fundamentals of creating 2D games in Unity. It explains key concepts such as sprites, animations, and collision detection with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to build a simple 2D game from scratch. The module emphasizes the importance of art, design, and physics in game development. It also covers best practices for optimizing performance in 2D projects. By the end, you will be able to develop engaging 2D games using Unity.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(136, 12, '3D Game Development', 
 'The "3D Game Development" module introduces you to the world of 3D game creation using Unity. It explains the basics of 3D modeling, lighting, and physics simulation with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to design a simple 3D environment. The module emphasizes the importance of spatial design and camera control in 3D games. It also covers techniques for performance optimization in 3D projects. By the end, you will be ready to build and customize 3D games in Unity.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(137, 12, 'Scripting with C#', 
 'In the "Scripting with C#" module, you will learn how to program game logic using C# in Unity. It explains the fundamentals of C# programming and how it integrates with Unity’s components with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to write scripts that control game behavior. The module emphasizes the importance of clean, maintainable code in game development. It also covers debugging techniques and best practices for scripting in Unity. By the end, you will be proficient in using C# to bring your games to life.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(138, 12, 'Physics in Unity', 
 'The "Physics in Unity" module focuses on applying physics to game objects for realistic behavior. It explains how to use rigidbodies, colliders, and forces with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that involve simulating real-world physics in games. The module emphasizes the importance of physics for immersive gameplay. It also discusses optimization techniques for physics calculations. Best practices for setting up and tuning physics properties are covered. By the end, you will be capable of creating dynamic and realistic game environments in Unity.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(139, 12, 'Animation Basics', 
 'In the "Animation Basics" module, you will learn how to animate characters and objects in Unity. It explains the animation system, keyframe techniques, and transitions with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to create simple animations using the Animator window. The module emphasizes the importance of smooth, realistic motion in enhancing gameplay. It also covers tips for blending animations and managing complex animation trees. By the end, you will be proficient in implementing basic animations in your Unity projects.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(140, 12, 'UI Design', 
 'The "UI Design" module teaches you how to create intuitive and appealing user interfaces in Unity. It explains the principles of UI layout, navigation, and user interaction with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to build menus, HUDs, and other UI elements. The module emphasizes the role of good UI design in enhancing the player experience. It also covers techniques for responsive design and dynamic UI updates. By the end, you will be able to design and implement effective UI systems in Unity.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(141, 12, 'Audio Integration', 
 'In the "Audio Integration" module, you will learn how to add sound effects and music to your Unity games. It explains how to import audio assets and use audio sources and listeners with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to synchronize audio with game events. The module emphasizes the importance of sound in creating an immersive gaming experience. It also covers best practices for managing audio performance. By the end, you will have the skills to effectively integrate audio into your game projects.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(142, 12, 'Game Optimization', 
 'The "Game Optimization" module focuses on techniques to improve the performance of your Unity games. It explains how to profile your game, optimize assets, and reduce load times with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to identify and fix performance bottlenecks. The module emphasizes the importance of optimization for a smooth gaming experience. It also covers best practices for memory management and rendering efficiency. By the end, you will be equipped with strategies to enhance the performance of your games.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(143, 12, 'Project: Create a Unity Game', 
 'In the "Project: Create a Unity Game" module, you will apply all that you have learned to develop a complete game using Unity. It guides you through game concept, design, development, and testing with detailed examples. The lesson includes hands-on exercises that simulate real-world game development challenges. The module emphasizes creativity, problem solving, and iterative improvement. It also covers project management and team collaboration aspects. By the end, you will have built a fully functional Unity game that showcases your skills.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(144, 12, 'Bonus: Advanced Unity Techniques', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced Unity Techniques" explores sophisticated methods to enhance your game development workflow. It explains advanced scripting, shader programming, and performance optimization with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to push the limits of what you can achieve in Unity. The module emphasizes continuous learning and innovation in game design. It also covers integrating third-party assets and custom tools. By the end, you will have advanced strategies to elevate your Unity game development projects.',
 12, 1, 400, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 13: Blockchain Fundamentals (Modules 145-156)
(145, 13, 'Introduction to Blockchain', 
 'In the "Introduction to Blockchain" module, you will learn the basic principles behind blockchain technology. It explains the concept of distributed ledgers and decentralization with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to explore blockchain structure and key components. The module emphasizes the disruptive potential of blockchain in various industries. It also covers the evolution of blockchain technology and its future prospects. Best practices for understanding complex blockchain concepts are discussed. By the end, you will have a strong foundational knowledge of blockchain.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(146, 13, 'How Blockchain Works', 
 'The "How Blockchain Works" module provides a detailed look at the inner workings of blockchain systems. It explains how blocks are created, linked, and secured with cryptographic techniques. Detailed examples illustrate the process of validating transactions and reaching consensus. The lesson includes exercises to simulate block creation and chain verification. The module emphasizes transparency and immutability as core features of blockchain. It also discusses potential challenges and limitations of current systems. By the end, you will understand the technical underpinnings of blockchain.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(147, 13, 'Cryptography in Blockchain', 
 'In the "Cryptography in Blockchain" module, you will learn how encryption and hashing secure blockchain data. It explains various cryptographic algorithms used to ensure data integrity with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that demonstrate how digital signatures and hash functions work. The module emphasizes the importance of cryptography in maintaining trust and security. It also covers common cryptographic vulnerabilities and mitigation strategies. By the end, you will be proficient in the cryptographic techniques that underpin blockchain technology.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(148, 13, 'Decentralization', 
 'The "Decentralization" module focuses on the benefits and challenges of decentralized systems. It explains how removing central authorities increases transparency and security with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that analyze the impact of decentralization in various applications. The module emphasizes the role of consensus mechanisms in achieving decentralization. It also discusses the potential for innovation and disruption in decentralized networks. By the end, you will understand how decentralization transforms traditional systems.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(149, 13, 'Smart Contracts', 
 'In the "Smart Contracts" module, you will learn about self-executing contracts that run on blockchain platforms. It explains how smart contracts automate agreements with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to write and test simple smart contracts. The module emphasizes the potential of smart contracts to reduce intermediaries and enhance trust. It also covers the challenges of security and scalability in contract execution. By the end, you will be able to develop and deploy basic smart contracts.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(150, 13, 'Blockchain Use Cases', 
 'The "Blockchain Use Cases" module explores various real-world applications of blockchain technology. It explains how blockchain is transforming industries such as finance, supply chain, and healthcare with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to analyze case studies and identify key benefits. The module emphasizes the versatility and innovation enabled by blockchain. It also discusses challenges and considerations for implementing blockchain solutions. By the end, you will be able to evaluate the potential of blockchain in different sectors.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(151, 13, 'Consensus Mechanisms', 
 'In the "Consensus Mechanisms" module, you will learn how blockchain networks agree on the validity of transactions. It explains various consensus algorithms such as proof-of-work and proof-of-stake with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that demonstrate the trade-offs between different methods. The module emphasizes the importance of consensus in maintaining network integrity. It also covers advanced consensus techniques and their impact on scalability. By the end, you will have a deep understanding of how consensus is achieved in blockchain systems.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(152, 13, 'Building a Simple Blockchain', 
 'The "Building a Simple Blockchain" module provides a hands-on approach to understanding blockchain technology. It explains how to implement a basic blockchain using a programming language with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to build, add blocks, and validate the chain. The module emphasizes practical learning through code and experimentation. It also discusses the challenges of scaling and securing a blockchain. By the end, you will have created a simple blockchain prototype.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(153, 13, 'Security in Blockchain', 
 'In the "Security in Blockchain" module, you will learn about the measures taken to secure blockchain networks. It explains how cryptographic techniques and decentralized validation ensure system integrity with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to analyze security vulnerabilities in blockchain systems. The module emphasizes the importance of robust security protocols in preventing fraud. It also discusses potential threats and mitigation strategies. By the end, you will be proficient in the security measures that protect blockchain networks.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(154, 13, 'Regulatory Considerations', 
 'The "Regulatory Considerations" module examines the legal and compliance aspects of blockchain technology. It explains how different jurisdictions approach blockchain regulation with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that explore the impact of regulations on blockchain adoption. The module emphasizes the importance of balancing innovation with legal compliance. It also covers emerging trends in blockchain policy and standards. By the end, you will understand the regulatory landscape affecting blockchain projects.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(155, 13, 'Future of Blockchain', 
 'In the "Future of Blockchain" module, you will explore upcoming trends and potential innovations in blockchain technology. It explains how blockchain may evolve and transform various industries with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to analyze future scenarios and technological advancements. The module emphasizes creative thinking and strategic planning in technology adoption. It also covers challenges and opportunities for blockchain in the coming years. By the end, you will have an informed perspective on the future impact of blockchain.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(156, 13, 'Bonus: Advanced Blockchain Applications', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced Blockchain Applications" focuses on cutting-edge uses of blockchain beyond cryptocurrencies. It explains innovative applications such as decentralized finance and supply chain tracking with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to explore advanced use cases and develop prototypes. The module emphasizes the transformative potential of blockchain in various fields. It also discusses scalability, interoperability, and emerging technologies. By the end, you will be equipped with advanced knowledge to pursue innovative blockchain projects.',
 12, 1, 300, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 14: Cloud Computing with AWS (Modules 157-168)
(157, 14, 'Introduction to AWS', 
 'In the "Introduction to AWS" module, you will learn about the fundamentals of Amazon Web Services and its cloud offerings. It explains the benefits of cloud computing and AWS’s role in the market with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to set up an AWS account and explore the console. The module emphasizes scalability, reliability, and cost-effectiveness. It also covers basic AWS terminology and services. By the end, you will have a strong foundation in AWS cloud computing.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(158, 14, 'AWS Core Services', 
 'The "AWS Core Services" module focuses on the essential services provided by AWS. It explains services such as EC2, S3, and RDS with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to launch instances and manage storage. The module emphasizes how these services work together to support scalable applications. It also covers best practices for security and performance in the cloud. By the end, you will be familiar with the core AWS services required for cloud solutions.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(159, 14, 'EC2 and Compute Services', 
 'In the "EC2 and Compute Services" module, you will learn how to deploy and manage virtual servers using AWS EC2. It explains instance types, configuration, and scaling with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to launch, configure, and monitor EC2 instances. The module emphasizes the importance of compute resources in cloud environments. It also covers security groups and cost management strategies. By the end, you will be proficient in managing compute services on AWS.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(160, 14, 'Storage Solutions', 
 'The "Storage Solutions" module focuses on the various storage options available in AWS. It explains the differences between S3, EBS, and Glacier with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to set up and manage different storage services. The module emphasizes scalability, durability, and cost-effectiveness in cloud storage. It also covers best practices for data backup and retrieval. By the end, you will be capable of selecting and configuring appropriate storage solutions in AWS.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(161, 14, 'Networking in AWS', 
 'In the "Networking in AWS" module, you will learn about the fundamentals of virtual networking using AWS. It explains VPCs, subnets, and routing with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to create and configure virtual networks. The module emphasizes secure connectivity and efficient network design. It also covers best practices for network segmentation and security. By the end, you will have the skills to build and manage networks in the AWS cloud.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(162, 14, 'AWS Security', 
 'The "AWS Security" module focuses on securing your AWS resources using built-in tools and best practices. It explains identity and access management (IAM), encryption, and monitoring with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to set up secure environments and test security configurations. The module emphasizes the importance of continuous security monitoring in the cloud. It also covers compliance standards and risk management strategies. By the end, you will be proficient in implementing security measures on AWS.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(163, 14, 'Database Services', 
 'In the "Database Services" module, you will learn about AWS database offerings such as RDS, DynamoDB, and Redshift. It explains the features and use cases of each service with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to launch and manage database instances. The module emphasizes scalability, reliability, and performance in cloud databases. It also covers best practices for backup, recovery, and security. By the end, you will be able to select and manage AWS database services effectively.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(164, 14, 'Serverless Computing', 
 'The "Serverless Computing" module introduces you to AWS Lambda and other serverless services. It explains how to run code without managing servers with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to deploy and trigger Lambda functions. The module emphasizes cost savings, scalability, and simplified operations. It also covers integration with other AWS services and best practices for serverless architectures. By the end, you will be proficient in developing serverless applications on AWS.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(165, 14, 'Monitoring and Management', 
 'In the "Monitoring and Management" module, you will learn how to keep track of your AWS resources using tools like CloudWatch. It explains metrics, logging, and alerts with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to set up dashboards and automate responses. The module emphasizes the importance of proactive monitoring in cloud environments. It also covers best practices for resource optimization and cost management. By the end, you will be able to effectively monitor and manage AWS services.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(166, 14, 'Cost Optimization', 
 'The "Cost Optimization" module focuses on strategies to manage and reduce AWS expenses. It explains cost allocation, budgeting, and resource optimization with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to analyze and adjust resource usage for cost efficiency. The module emphasizes the importance of continuous cost monitoring in the cloud. It also covers best practices for selecting cost-effective services and scaling resources appropriately. By the end, you will be proficient in optimizing your AWS costs without compromising performance.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(167, 14, 'Case Study: AWS in Action', 
 'In the "Case Study: AWS in Action" module, you will analyze real-world examples of AWS implementations. It explains how organizations use AWS to solve complex business challenges with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to evaluate the strategies and outcomes of these case studies. The module emphasizes learning from practical experiences and best practices. It also covers challenges and innovations in cloud computing. By the end, you will gain insights into effective AWS deployments in various industries.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(168, 14, 'Bonus: Advanced AWS Architecting', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced AWS Architecting" focuses on designing robust and scalable AWS infrastructures. It explains advanced concepts such as multi-region deployments and hybrid architectures with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to design and simulate complex architectures. The module emphasizes security, performance, and cost considerations in large-scale deployments. It also covers emerging trends and tools for advanced cloud management. By the end, you will have advanced strategies to architect efficient and resilient AWS solutions.',
 12, 1, 350, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),

-- Course 15: Artificial Intelligence in Practice (Modules 169-180)
(169, 15, 'Introduction to AI', 
 'In the "Introduction to AI" module, you will learn the basic concepts of artificial intelligence and its applications. It explains the evolution of AI and its impact on various industries with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that introduce fundamental AI terminology and concepts. The module emphasizes the importance of data and algorithms in driving AI. It also covers ethical considerations and future trends in AI. Best practices for approaching AI problems are discussed. By the end, you will have a strong foundational understanding of artificial intelligence.',
 1, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(170, 15, 'AI and Machine Learning', 
 'The "AI and Machine Learning" module explores the relationship between AI and machine learning. It explains how machines learn from data to perform intelligent tasks with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that illustrate model training and evaluation. The module emphasizes the transformative potential of machine learning in various sectors. It also covers the challenges of data quality and model bias. Best practices for integrating AI and machine learning are discussed. By the end, you will be able to differentiate between AI and machine learning concepts clearly.',
 2, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(171, 15, 'Neural Networks Deep Dive', 
 'In the "Neural Networks Deep Dive" module, you will explore the architecture and functioning of neural networks. It explains layers, activation functions, and backpropagation with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that require you to build and train simple neural network models. The module emphasizes the iterative nature of training neural networks and the importance of parameter tuning. It also covers common challenges such as vanishing gradients. By the end, you will have an in-depth understanding of neural network structures.',
 3, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(172, 15, 'Natural Language Processing', 
 'The "Natural Language Processing" module focuses on the techniques for processing and analyzing human language using AI. It explains concepts such as tokenization, sentiment analysis, and language modeling with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to build simple NLP applications. The module emphasizes the importance of context and semantics in language understanding. It also covers challenges unique to processing natural language. By the end, you will be equipped with basic NLP techniques for real-world applications.',
 4, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(173, 15, 'Computer Vision', 
 'In the "Computer Vision" module, you will learn how AI can be used to interpret and process images and videos. It explains techniques for object detection, image classification, and segmentation with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that demonstrate practical computer vision applications. The module emphasizes the importance of feature extraction and deep learning in visual tasks. It also covers challenges such as varying lighting conditions and occlusion. By the end, you will have a strong understanding of how computer vision algorithms work.',
 5, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(174, 15, 'Reinforcement Learning', 
 'The "Reinforcement Learning" module introduces you to an area of AI where agents learn by interacting with an environment. It explains the concepts of rewards, actions, and policy learning with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that simulate reinforcement learning scenarios. The module emphasizes the trial-and-error nature of reinforcement learning and its real-world applications. It also covers common algorithms such as Q-learning and policy gradients. By the end, you will understand how reinforcement learning drives decision-making processes.',
 6, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(175, 15, 'Ethics in AI', 
 'In the "Ethics in AI" module, you will explore the moral and ethical considerations surrounding artificial intelligence. It explains topics such as bias, fairness, and accountability with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that provoke critical thinking about the societal impacts of AI. The module emphasizes the importance of responsible AI development and transparency. It also covers regulatory and policy challenges related to AI deployment. By the end, you will be able to identify and address ethical issues in AI systems.',
 7, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(176, 15, 'Data Preparation for AI', 
 'The "Data Preparation for AI" module focuses on the crucial process of cleaning and organizing data for AI models. It explains techniques for handling missing values, normalization, and feature extraction with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to prepare datasets for machine learning. The module emphasizes that high-quality data is the foundation of effective AI. It also covers challenges such as data imbalance and noise. By the end, you will be proficient in preparing data for AI applications.',
 8, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(177, 15, 'Model Training and Evaluation', 
 'In the "Model Training and Evaluation" module, you will learn how to train AI models and measure their performance. It explains training techniques, loss functions, and evaluation metrics with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to optimize and test models using real-world datasets. The module emphasizes the iterative nature of model development and validation. It also covers strategies for hyperparameter tuning and cross-validation. By the end, you will have the skills to train and assess AI models effectively.',
 9, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(178, 15, 'Deployment of AI Solutions', 
 'The "Deployment of AI Solutions" module teaches you how to take AI models from development to production. It explains the challenges of integrating AI systems into existing applications with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to deploy a model using cloud services or on-premise solutions. The module emphasizes the importance of scalability, security, and monitoring in AI deployment. It also covers best practices for maintaining and updating deployed models. By the end, you will be ready to implement AI solutions in real-world environments.',
 10, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(179, 15, 'Case Studies in AI', 
 'In the "Case Studies in AI" module, you will analyze real-world applications of artificial intelligence across different industries. It explains how various organizations have leveraged AI to solve complex problems with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises that encourage you to evaluate the effectiveness of different AI approaches. The module emphasizes learning from practical implementations and industry best practices. It also covers challenges encountered and lessons learned from these case studies. By the end, you will have a broad perspective on AI’s practical impact.',
 11, 0, 0, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg'),
(180, 15, 'Bonus: Advanced AI Model Optimization', 
 'The bonus module "Advanced AI Model Optimization" delves into techniques for fine-tuning AI models for peak performance. It explains advanced optimization methods including model pruning, quantization, and ensemble techniques with detailed examples. The lesson includes exercises to experiment with different optimization strategies on complex models. The module emphasizes the importance of continuous improvement and adaptation in AI. It also discusses the trade-offs between model complexity and performance. By the end, you will be equipped with advanced strategies to enhance your AI models.',
 12, 1, 450, 'ms-appx:///Assets/image.jpg');

